ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you are a theory person, you simply cannot pass it up.
If you like montage or Vertov, it's pretty solid- a lot of discussion, if that's what you're into. We didn't do too much with collage. The professor is great though.
Yes! The films we watched were great and I learned a great deal about the subject. I believe that this class greatly influenced the rest of my work this semester in a positive way.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I wrote my undergraduate senior thesis for this class, so it was pretty important, yeah.
Opened up a bit my view of how we can take in and organize information, which was helpful in my art.
It helped me think about the variety of ways that montage has been used and can be used in the future.
